response: "{ \"title\": \"Easy: Sum of Cubes\", \"description\": \"Given a list of integers, calculate the sum of cubes of all numbers from 1 to n.\\n\\n#### Function Signature\\n```python\\ndef sum_of_cubes(n: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input\\n- `n` (int): The upper limit for calculating the sum of cubes.\\n\\n#### Output\\n- Returns the sum of cubes of all numbers from 1 to `n`.\", \"code\": \"def sum_of_cubes(n: int) -> int:\\n    total_sum = 0\\n    for i in range(1, n+1):\\n        total_sum += i ** 3\\n    return total_sum\\n\", \"tests\": [\"assert sum_of_cubes(3) == 36\", \"assert sum_of_cubes(10) == 2640\", \"assert sum_of_cubes(5) == 225\"] }"
